@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - dataflow/Application
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired Application spec, tracked status,\nand delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetApplication;
else (no)
:Create the OCI resource via CreateApplication\nwhen no tracked identity is present;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteApplication with\nrequired via GetApplication to NOT_FOUND\nconfirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetApplication until OCI\nreaches NOT_FOUND;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in DELETED;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE, INACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the imported\nfield surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartment_id, type;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateApplication only for mutable\nfields application_log_config, archive_uri,\narguments, class_name (+22 more);
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Return success for the ACTIVE, INACTIVE\nsuccess state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: dataflow
slug: application
kind: Application
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: terminating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete DELETED
supported drift: application_log_config,
archive_uri, arguments, class_name (+22 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id, type
create-only fields: none
list lookup: none
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
The active Application runtime is still the
handwritten override in
`pkg/servicemanager/dataflow/application`; this
seeded formal row exists to regenerate a
generatedruntime baseline without switching the
active reconcile path.
Create and update treat OCI `ACTIVE` and
`INACTIVE` as successful observed states,
project the live Application payload into
status, and reject create-only drift for
`compartmentId` and `type`.
The handwritten runtime never binds by list
lookup. Delete stays finalizer-backed for the
tracked OCID until `GetApplication` returns not
found; if OCI ever echoes lifecycle `DELETED`,
the runtime still treats that as terminating
instead of final completion.
end note
@enduml
